{"key":"post-8977716","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8977716</id>\n<content>Since a bulk substrate has such a large surface area, a few hours is plenty.&amp;nbsp; Remove any polyfill from the holes and use gently running water such as the bathtub faucet, and let it fill up and run out the holes.&amp;nbsp; After an hour or two, maybe three, dump out any excess water and return to fruiting conditions.&amp;nbsp; 24 hours will waterlog a bulk substrate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8977748</next>\n<prev>8977415</prev>\n<first>8971644</first>\n<last>8978026</last>\n<when>1222271614</when>\n<utime>09/24/08 06:53 PM</utime>\n</post>"}